abstract: Canada announces that 10,000 of planned 25,000 Syrian refugees will enter country in 2015; says remaining 15,000 will come by end of February 2016 when proper housing and services are available.
lead_paragraph: Several cabinet ministers said that only 10,000 of the planned 25,000 refugees would arrive by the end of the year.

headline.main: Canada: Syrians’ Arrival Is Delayed, and Officials Cite Need to Prepare
